{title: Shopping For Dresses}
{artist: Merle Haggard}
{composer: Written by Jimmie Dickens and Merle Haggard}

[3/4 time]

[C]Down through the ages men have [F]died for their women
And they've [C]done so so many [G7]times
[C]But each time I loved one I [F]always lost one
And I [C]guess the right one is [G7]so hard to [C]find

So I'm shopping for dresses with [F]no one to wear them
One [C]in each color and one in each [G7]style
Maybe [C]someday I'll find me a [F]lady to wear them
And [C]my shopping will be [G7]done for a [C]while

I bet somewhere a lady is [F]shopping for britches
Com[C]paring the value and appraising each [G7]pair
Maybe [C]someday the good Lord [F]will get us together
And [C]we'll both have a new [G7]wardrobe to [C]wear
Repeat #2